223/*
224** Convert 'nvar', a compiler index level, to its corresponding
225** register. For that, search for the highest variable below that level
226** that is in a register and uses its register index ('ridx') plus one.
227*/
228static int reglevel (FuncState *fs, int nvar) {
229 while (nvar-- > 0) {
230 Vardesc *vd = getlocalvardesc(fs, nvar); /* get previous variable */
231 if (vd->vd.kind != RDKCTC) /* is in a register? */
232 return vd->vd.ridx + 1;
233 }
234 return 0; /* no variables in registers */
235}

238/*
239** Return the number of variables in the register stack for the given
240** function.
241*/
242int luaY_nvarstack (FuncState *fs) {
243 return reglevel(fs, fs->nactvar);
244}

250static LocVar *localdebuginfo (FuncState *fs, int vidx) {

273/*
274** Raises an error if variable described by 'e' is read only
275*/
276static void check_readonly (LexState *ls, expdesc *e) {
277 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
278 TString *varname = NULL; /* to be set if variable is const */
279 switch (e->k) {
280 case VCONST: {
281 varname = ls->dyd->actvar.arr[e->u.info].vd.name;
282 break;
283 }
284 case VLOCAL: {
285 Vardesc *vardesc = getlocalvardesc(fs, e->u.var.vidx);
286 if (vardesc->vd.kind != VDKREG) /* not a regular variable? */
287 varname = vardesc->vd.name;
288 break;
289 }
290 case VUPVAL: {
291 Upvaldesc *up = &fs->f->upvalues[e->u.info];
292 if (up->kind != VDKREG)
293 varname = up->name;
294 break;
295 }
296 default:
297 return; /* other cases cannot be read-only */
298 }
299 if (varname) {
300 const char *msg = luaO_pushfstring(ls->L,
301 "attempt to assign to const variable '%s'", getstr(varname));
302 luaK_semerror(ls, msg); /* error */
303 }
304}

310static void adjustlocalvars (LexState *ls, int nvars) {
311 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
312 int reglevel = luaY_nvarstack(fs);
313 int i;
314 for (i = 0; i < nvars; i++) {
315 int vidx = fs->nactvar++;
316 Vardesc *var = getlocalvardesc(fs, vidx);
317 var->vd.ridx = reglevel++;
318 var->vd.pidx = registerlocalvar(ls, fs, var->vd.name);
319 }

351static Upvaldesc *allocupvalue (FuncState *fs) {
352 Proto *f = fs->f;
353 int oldsize = f->sizeupvalues;
354 checklimit(fs, fs->nups + 1, MAXUPVAL, "upvalues");
355 luaM_growvector(fs->ls->L, f->upvalues, fs->nups, f->sizeupvalues,
356 Upvaldesc, MAXUPVAL, "upvalues");
357 while (oldsize < f->sizeupvalues)
358 f->upvalues[oldsize++].name = NULL;
359 return &f->upvalues[fs->nups++];
360}

363static int newupvalue (FuncState *fs, TString *name, expdesc *v) {
364 Upvaldesc *up = allocupvalue(fs);
365 FuncState *prev = fs->prev;
366 if (v->k == VLOCAL) {
367 up->instack = 1;
368 up->idx = v->u.var.ridx;
369 up->kind = getlocalvardesc(prev, v->u.var.vidx)->vd.kind;
370 lua_assert(eqstr(name, getlocalvardesc(prev, v->u.var.vidx)->vd.name));
371 }
372 else {
373 up->instack = 0;
374 up->idx = cast_byte(v->u.info);
375 up->kind = prev->f->upvalues[v->u.info].kind;
376 lua_assert(eqstr(name, prev->f->upvalues[v->u.info].name));
377 }
378 up->name = name;
379 luaC_objbarrier(fs->ls->L, fs->f, name);
380 return fs->nups - 1;
381}

384/*
385** Look for an active local variable with the name 'n' in the
386** function 'fs'. If found, initialize 'var' with it and return
387** its expression kind; otherwise return -1.
388*/
389static int searchvar (FuncState *fs, TString *n, expdesc *var) {
390 int i;
391 for (i = cast_int(fs->nactvar) - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
392 Vardesc *vd = getlocalvardesc(fs, i);
393 if (eqstr(n, vd->vd.name)) { /* found? */
394 if (vd->vd.kind == RDKCTC) /* compile-time constant? */
395 init_exp(var, VCONST, fs->firstlocal + i);
396 else /* real variable */
397 init_var(fs, var, i);
398 return var->k;
399 }
400 }
401 return -1; /* not found */
402}

429/*
430** Find a variable with the given name 'n'. If it is an upvalue, add
431** this upvalue into all intermediate functions. If it is a global, set
432** 'var' as 'void' as a flag.
433*/
434static void singlevaraux (FuncState *fs, TString *n, expdesc *var, int base) {
435 if (fs == NULL) /* no more levels? */
436 init_exp(var, VVOID, 0); /* default is global */
437 else {
438 int v = searchvar(fs, n, var); /* look up locals at current level */
439 if (v >= 0) { /* found? */
440 if (v == VLOCAL && !base)
441 markupval(fs, var->u.var.vidx); /* local will be used as an upval */
442 }
443 else { /* not found as local at current level; try upvalues */
444 int idx = searchupvalue(fs, n); /* try existing upvalues */
445 if (idx < 0) { /* not found? */
446 singlevaraux(fs->prev, n, var, 0); /* try upper levels */
447 if (var->k == VLOCAL || var->k == VUPVAL) /* local or upvalue? */
448 idx = newupvalue(fs, n, var); /* will be a new upvalue */
449 else /* it is a global or a constant */
450 return; /* don't need to do anything at this level */
451 }
452 init_exp(var, VUPVAL, idx); /* new or old upvalue */
453 }
454 }
455}

458/*
459** Find a variable with the given name 'n', handling global variables
460** too.
461*/
462static void singlevar (LexState *ls, expdesc *var) {
463 TString *varname = str_checkname(ls);
464 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
465 singlevaraux(fs, varname, var, 1);
466 if (var->k == VVOID) { /* global name? */
467 expdesc key;
468 singlevaraux(fs, ls->envn, var, 1); /* get environment variable */
469 lua_assert(var->k != VVOID); /* this one must exist */
470 codestring(&key, varname); /* key is variable name */
471 luaK_indexed(fs, var, &key); /* env[varname] */
472 }
473}

476/*
477** Adjust the number of results from an expression list 'e' with 'nexps'
478** expressions to 'nvars' values.
479*/
480static void adjust_assign (LexState *ls, int nvars, int nexps, expdesc *e) {
481 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
482 int needed = nvars - nexps; /* extra values needed */
483 if (hasmultret(e->k)) { /* last expression has multiple returns? */
484 int extra = needed + 1; /* discount last expression itself */
485 if (extra < 0)
486 extra = 0;
487 luaK_setreturns(fs, e, extra); /* last exp. provides the difference */
488 }
489 else {
490 if (e->k != VVOID) /* at least one expression? */
491 luaK_exp2nextreg(fs, e); /* close last expression */
492 if (needed > 0) /* missing values? */
493 luaK_nil(fs, fs->freereg, needed); /* complete with nils */
494 }
495 if (needed > 0)
496 luaK_reserveregs(fs, needed); /* registers for extra values */
497 else /* adding 'needed' is actually a subtraction */
498 fs->freereg += needed; /* remove extra values */
499}

512static l_noret jumpscopeerror (LexState *ls, Labeldesc *gt) {

520/*
521** Solves the goto at index 'g' to given 'label' and removes it
522** from the list of pending goto's.
523** If it jumps into the scope of some variable, raises an error.
524*/
525static void solvegoto (LexState *ls, int g, Labeldesc *label) {
526 int i;
527 Labellist *gl = &ls->dyd->gt; /* list of goto's */
528 Labeldesc *gt = &gl->arr[g]; /* goto to be resolved */
529 lua_assert(eqstr(gt->name, label->name));
530 if (l_unlikely(gt->nactvar < label->nactvar)) /* enter some scope? */
531 jumpscopeerror(ls, gt);
532 luaK_patchlist(ls->fs, gt->pc, label->pc);
533 for (i = g; i < gl->n - 1; i++) /* remove goto from pending list */
534 gl->arr[i] = gl->arr[i + 1];
535 gl->n--;
536}

548 if (eqstr(lb->name, name)) /* correct label? */
549 return lb;

558static int newlabelentry (LexState *ls, Labellist *l, TString *name,

578/*
579** Solves forward jumps. Check whether new label 'lb' matches any
580** pending gotos in current block and solves them. Return true
581** if any of the goto's need to close upvalues.
582*/
583static int solvegotos (LexState *ls, Labeldesc *lb) {
584 Labellist *gl = &ls->dyd->gt;
585 int i = ls->fs->bl->firstgoto;
586 int needsclose = 0;
587 while (i < gl->n) {
588 if (eqstr(gl->arr[i].name, lb->name)) {
589 needsclose |= gl->arr[i].close;
590 solvegoto(ls, i, lb); /* will remove 'i' from the list */
591 }
592 else
593 i++;
594 }
595 return needsclose;
596}

599/*
600** Create a new label with the given 'name' at the given 'line'.
601** 'last' tells whether label is the last non-op statement in its
602** block. Solves all pending goto's to this new label and adds
603** a close instruction if necessary.
604** Returns true iff it added a close instruction.
605*/
606static int createlabel (LexState *ls, TString *name, int line,
607 int last) {
608 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
609 Labellist *ll = &ls->dyd->label;
610 int l = newlabelentry(ls, ll, name, line, luaK_getlabel(fs));
611 if (last) { /* label is last no-op statement in the block? */
612 /* assume that locals are already out of scope */
613 ll->arr[l].nactvar = fs->bl->nactvar;
614 }
615 if (solvegotos(ls, &ll->arr[l])) { /* need close? */
616 luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_CLOSE, luaY_nvarstack(fs), 0, 0);
617 return 1;
618 }
619 return 0;
620}

623/*
624** Adjust pending gotos to outer level of a block.
625*/
626static void movegotosout (FuncState *fs, BlockCnt *bl) {
627 int i;
628 Labellist *gl = &fs->ls->dyd->gt;
629 /* correct pending gotos to current block */
630 for (i = bl->firstgoto; i < gl->n; i++) { /* for each pending goto */
631 Labeldesc *gt = &gl->arr[i];
632 /* leaving a variable scope? */
633 if (reglevel(fs, gt->nactvar) > reglevel(fs, bl->nactvar))
634 gt->close |= bl->upval; /* jump may need a close */
635 gt->nactvar = bl->nactvar; /* update goto level */
636 }
637}

640static void enterblock (FuncState *fs, BlockCnt *bl, lu_byte isloop) {
641 bl->isloop = isloop;
642 bl->nactvar = fs->nactvar;
643 bl->firstlabel = fs->ls->dyd->label.n;
644 bl->firstgoto = fs->ls->dyd->gt.n;
645 bl->upval = 0;
646 bl->insidetbc = (fs->bl != NULL && fs->bl->insidetbc);
647 bl->previous = fs->bl;
648 fs->bl = bl;
649 lua_assert(fs->freereg == luaY_nvarstack(fs));
650}

653/*
654** generates an error for an undefined 'goto'.
655*/
656static l_noret undefgoto (LexState *ls, Labeldesc *gt) {
657 const char *msg;
658 if (eqstr(gt->name, luaS_newliteral(ls->L, "break"))) {
659 msg = "break outside loop at line %d";
660 msg = luaO_pushfstring(ls->L, msg, gt->line);
661 }
662 else {
663 msg = "no visible label '%s' for <goto> at line %d";
664 msg = luaO_pushfstring(ls->L, msg, getstr(gt->name), gt->line);
665 }
666 luaK_semerror(ls, msg);
667}
668
669
670static void leaveblock (FuncState *fs) {
671 BlockCnt *bl = fs->bl;
672 LexState *ls = fs->ls;
673 int hasclose = 0;
674 int stklevel = reglevel(fs, bl->nactvar); /* level outside the block */
675 if (bl->isloop) /* fix pending breaks? */
676 hasclose = createlabel(ls, luaS_newliteral(ls->L, "break"), 0, 0);
677 if (!hasclose && bl->previous && bl->upval)
678 luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_CLOSE, stklevel, 0, 0);
679 fs->bl = bl->previous;
680 removevars(fs, bl->nactvar);
681 lua_assert(bl->nactvar == fs->nactvar);
682 fs->freereg = stklevel; /* free registers */
683 ls->dyd->label.n = bl->firstlabel; /* remove local labels */
684 if (bl->previous) /* inner block? */
685 movegotosout(fs, bl); /* update pending gotos to outer block */
686 else {
687 if (bl->firstgoto < ls->dyd->gt.n) /* pending gotos in outer block? */
688 undefgoto(ls, &ls->dyd->gt.arr[bl->firstgoto]); /* error */
689 }
690}
691
692
693/*
694** adds a new prototype into list of prototypes
695*/
696static Proto *addprototype (LexState *ls) {
697 Proto *clp;
698 lua_State *L = ls->L;
699 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
700 Proto *f = fs->f; /* prototype of current function */
701 if (fs->np >= f->sizep) {
702 int oldsize = f->sizep;
703 luaM_growvector(L, f->p, fs->np, f->sizep, Proto *, MAXARG_Bx, "functions");
704 while (oldsize < f->sizep)
705 f->p[oldsize++] = NULL;
706 }
707 f->p[fs->np++] = clp = luaF_newproto(L);
708 luaC_objbarrier(L, f, clp);
709 return clp;
710}
711
712
713/*
714** codes instruction to create new closure in parent function.
715** The OP_CLOSURE instruction uses the last available register,
716** so that, if it invokes the GC, the GC knows which registers
717** are in use at that time.
718
719*/
720static void codeclosure (LexState *ls, expdesc *v) {
721 FuncState *fs = ls->fs->prev;
722 init_exp(v, VRELOC, luaK_codeABx(fs, OP_CLOSURE, 0, fs->np - 1));
723 luaK_exp2nextreg(fs, v); /* fix it at the last register */
724}
725
726
727static void open_func (LexState *ls, FuncState *fs, BlockCnt *bl) {
728 Proto *f = fs->f;
729 fs->prev = ls->fs; /* linked list of funcstates */
730 fs->ls = ls;
731 ls->fs = fs;
732 fs->pc = 0;
733 fs->previousline = f->linedefined;
734 fs->iwthabs = 0;
735 fs->lasttarget = 0;
736 fs->freereg = 0;
737 fs->nk = 0;
738 fs->nabslineinfo = 0;
739 fs->np = 0;
740 fs->nups = 0;
741 fs->ndebugvars = 0;
742 fs->nactvar = 0;
743 fs->needclose = 0;
744 fs->firstlocal = ls->dyd->actvar.n;
745 fs->firstlabel = ls->dyd->label.n;
746 fs->bl = NULL;
747 f->source = ls->source;
748 luaC_objbarrier(ls->L, f, f->source);
749 f->maxstacksize = 2; /* registers 0/1 are always valid */
750 enterblock(fs, bl, 0);
751}
752
753
754static void close_func (LexState *ls) {
755 lua_State *L = ls->L;
756 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
757 Proto *f = fs->f;
758 luaK_ret(fs, luaY_nvarstack(fs), 0); /* final return */
759 leaveblock(fs);
760 lua_assert(fs->bl == NULL);
761 luaK_finish(fs);
762 luaM_shrinkvector(L, f->code, f->sizecode, fs->pc, Instruction);
763 luaM_shrinkvector(L, f->lineinfo, f->sizelineinfo, fs->pc, ls_byte);
764 luaM_shrinkvector(L, f->abslineinfo, f->sizeabslineinfo,
765 fs->nabslineinfo, AbsLineInfo);
766 luaM_shrinkvector(L, f->k, f->sizek, fs->nk, TValue);
767 luaM_shrinkvector(L, f->p, f->sizep, fs->np, Proto *);
768 luaM_shrinkvector(L, f->locvars, f->sizelocvars, fs->ndebugvars, LocVar);
769 luaM_shrinkvector(L, f->upvalues, f->sizeupvalues, fs->nups, Upvaldesc);
770 ls->fs = fs->prev;
771 luaC_checkGC(L);
772}

781/*
782** check whether current token is in the follow set of a block.
783** 'until' closes syntactical blocks, but do not close scope,
784** so it is handled in separate.
785*/
786static int block_follow (LexState *ls, int withuntil) {
787 switch (ls->t.token) {
788 case TK_ELSE: case TK_ELSEIF:
789 case TK_END: case TK_EOS:
790 return 1;
791 case TK_UNTIL: return withuntil;
792 default: return 0;
793 }
794}
795
796
797static void statlist (LexState *ls) {
798 /* statlist -> { stat [';'] } */
799 while (!block_follow(ls, 1)) {
800 if (ls->t.token == TK_RETURN) {
801 statement(ls);
802 return; /* 'return' must be last statement */
803 }
804 statement(ls);
805 }
806}
807
808
809static void fieldsel (LexState *ls, expdesc *v) {
810 /* fieldsel -> ['.' | ':'] NAME */
811 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
812 expdesc key;
813 luaK_exp2anyregup(fs, v);
814 luaX_next(ls); /* skip the dot or colon */
815 codename(ls, &key);
816 luaK_indexed(fs, v, &key);
817}
818
819
820static void yindex (LexState *ls, expdesc *v) {
821 /* index -> '[' expr ']' */
822 luaX_next(ls); /* skip the '[' */
823 expr(ls, v);
824 luaK_exp2val(ls->fs, v);
825 checknext(ls, ']');
826}

829/*
830** {======================================================================
831** Rules for Constructors
832** =======================================================================
833*/
834
835
836typedef struct ConsControl {
837 expdesc v; /* last list item read */
838 expdesc *t; /* table descriptor */
839 int nh; /* total number of 'record' elements */
840 int na; /* number of array elements already stored */
841 int tostore; /* number of array elements pending to be stored */
842} ConsControl;
843
844
845static void recfield (LexState *ls, ConsControl *cc) {
846 /* recfield -> (NAME | '['exp']') = exp */
847 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
848 int reg = ls->fs->freereg;
849 expdesc tab, key, val;
850 if (ls->t.token == TK_NAME) {
851 checklimit(fs, cc->nh, MAX_INT, "items in a constructor");
852 codename(ls, &key);
853 }
854 else /* ls->t.token == '[' */
855 yindex(ls, &key);
856 cc->nh++;
857 checknext(ls, '=');
858 tab = *cc->t;
859 luaK_indexed(fs, &tab, &key);
860 expr(ls, &val);
861 luaK_storevar(fs, &tab, &val);
862 fs->freereg = reg; /* free registers */
863}
864
865
866static void closelistfield (FuncState *fs, ConsControl *cc) {
867 if (cc->v.k == VVOID) return; /* there is no list item */
868 luaK_exp2nextreg(fs, &cc->v);
869 cc->v.k = VVOID;
870 if (cc->tostore == LFIELDS_PER_FLUSH) {
871 luaK_setlist(fs, cc->t->u.info, cc->na, cc->tostore); /* flush */
872 cc->na += cc->tostore;
873 cc->tostore = 0; /* no more items pending */
874 }
875}
876
877
878static void lastlistfield (FuncState *fs, ConsControl *cc) {
879 if (cc->tostore == 0) return;
880 if (hasmultret(cc->v.k)) {
881 luaK_setmultret(fs, &cc->v);
882 luaK_setlist(fs, cc->t->u.info, cc->na, LUA_MULTRET);
883 cc->na--; /* do not count last expression (unknown number of elements) */
884 }
885 else {
886 if (cc->v.k != VVOID)
887 luaK_exp2nextreg(fs, &cc->v);
888 luaK_setlist(fs, cc->t->u.info, cc->na, cc->tostore);
889 }
890 cc->na += cc->tostore;
891}
892
893
894static void listfield (LexState *ls, ConsControl *cc) {
895 /* listfield -> exp */
896 expr(ls, &cc->v);
897 cc->tostore++;
898}
899
900
901static void field (LexState *ls, ConsControl *cc) {
902 /* field -> listfield | recfield */
903 switch(ls->t.token) {
904 case TK_NAME: { /* may be 'listfield' or 'recfield' */
905 if (luaX_lookahead(ls) != '=') /* expression? */
906 listfield(ls, cc);
907 else
908 recfield(ls, cc);
909 break;
910 }
911 case '[': {
912 recfield(ls, cc);
913 break;
914 }
915 default: {
916 listfield(ls, cc);
917 break;
918 }
919 }
920}
921
922
923static void constructor (LexState *ls, expdesc *t) {
924 /* constructor -> '{' [ field { sep field } [sep] ] '}'
925 sep -> ',' | ';' */
926 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
927 int line = ls->linenumber;
928 int pc = luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_NEWTABLE, 0, 0, 0);
929 ConsControl cc;
930 luaK_code(fs, 0); /* space for extra arg. */
931 cc.na = cc.nh = cc.tostore = 0;
932 cc.t = t;
933 init_exp(t, VNONRELOC, fs->freereg); /* table will be at stack top */
934 luaK_reserveregs(fs, 1);
935 init_exp(&cc.v, VVOID, 0); /* no value (yet) */
936 checknext(ls, '{');
937 do {
938 lua_assert(cc.v.k == VVOID || cc.tostore > 0);
939 if (ls->t.token == '}') break;
940 closelistfield(fs, &cc);
941 field(ls, &cc);
942 } while (testnext(ls, ',') || testnext(ls, ';'));
943 check_match(ls, '}', '{', line);
944 lastlistfield(fs, &cc);
945 luaK_settablesize(fs, pc, t->u.info, cc.na, cc.nh);
946}
947
948/* }====================================================================== */

950
951static void setvararg (FuncState *fs, int nparams) {
952 fs->f->is_vararg = 1;
953 luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_VARARGPREP, nparams, 0, 0);
954}
955
956
957static void parlist (LexState *ls) {
958 /* parlist -> [ {NAME ','} (NAME | '...') ] */
959 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
960 Proto *f = fs->f;
961 int nparams = 0;
962 int isvararg = 0;
963 if (ls->t.token != ')') { /* is 'parlist' not empty? */
964 do {
965 switch (ls->t.token) {
966 case TK_NAME: {
967 new_localvar(ls, str_checkname(ls));
968 nparams++;
969 break;
970 }
971 case TK_DOTS: {
972 luaX_next(ls);
973 isvararg = 1;
974 break;
975 }
976 default: luaX_syntaxerror(ls, "<name> or '...' expected");
977 }
978 } while (!isvararg && testnext(ls, ','));
979 }
980 adjustlocalvars(ls, nparams);
981 f->numparams = cast_byte(fs->nactvar);
982 if (isvararg)
983 setvararg(fs, f->numparams); /* declared vararg */
984 luaK_reserveregs(fs, fs->nactvar); /* reserve registers for parameters */
985}
986
987
988static void body (LexState *ls, expdesc *e, int ismethod, int line) {
989 /* body -> '(' parlist ')' block END */
990 FuncState new_fs;
991 BlockCnt bl;
992 new_fs.f = addprototype(ls);
993 new_fs.f->linedefined = line;
994 open_func(ls, &new_fs, &bl);
995 checknext(ls, '(');
996 if (ismethod) {
997 new_localvarliteral(ls, "self"); /* create 'self' parameter */
998 adjustlocalvars(ls, 1);
999 }
1000 parlist(ls);
1001 checknext(ls, ')');
1002 statlist(ls);
1003 new_fs.f->lastlinedefined = ls->linenumber;
1004 check_match(ls, TK_END, TK_FUNCTION, line);
1005 codeclosure(ls, e);
1006 close_func(ls);
1007}
1008
1009
1010static int explist (LexState *ls, expdesc *v) {
1011 /* explist -> expr { ',' expr } */
1012 int n = 1; /* at least one expression */
1013 expr(ls, v);
1014 while (testnext(ls, ',')) {
1015 luaK_exp2nextreg(ls->fs, v);
1016 expr(ls, v);
1017 n++;
1018 }
1019 return n;
1020}
1021
1022
1023static void funcargs (LexState *ls, expdesc *f, int line) {
1024 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1025 expdesc args;
1026 int base, nparams;
1027 switch (ls->t.token) {
1028 case '(': { /* funcargs -> '(' [ explist ] ')' */
1029 luaX_next(ls);
1030 if (ls->t.token == ')') /* arg list is empty? */
1031 args.k = VVOID;
1032 else {
1033 explist(ls, &args);
1034 if (hasmultret(args.k))
1035 luaK_setmultret(fs, &args);
1036 }
1037 check_match(ls, ')', '(', line);
1038 break;
1039 }
1040 case '{': { /* funcargs -> constructor */
1041 constructor(ls, &args);
1042 break;
1043 }
1044 case TK_STRING: { /* funcargs -> STRING */
1045 codestring(&args, ls->t.seminfo.ts);
1046 luaX_next(ls); /* must use 'seminfo' before 'next' */
1047 break;
1048 }
1049 default: {
1050 luaX_syntaxerror(ls, "function arguments expected");
1051 }
1052 }
1053 lua_assert(f->k == VNONRELOC);
1054 base = f->u.info; /* base register for call */
1055 if (hasmultret(args.k))
1056 nparams = LUA_MULTRET; /* open call */
1057 else {
1058 if (args.k != VVOID)
1059 luaK_exp2nextreg(fs, &args); /* close last argument */
1060 nparams = fs->freereg - (base+1);
1061 }
1062 init_exp(f, VCALL, luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_CALL, base, nparams+1, 2));
1063 luaK_fixline(fs, line);
1064 fs->freereg = base+1; /* call remove function and arguments and leaves
1065 (unless changed) one result */
1066}

1077
1078static void primaryexp (LexState *ls, expdesc *v) {
1079 /* primaryexp -> NAME | '(' expr ')' */
1080 switch (ls->t.token) {
1081 case '(': {
1082 int line = ls->linenumber;
1083 luaX_next(ls);
1084 expr(ls, v);
1085 check_match(ls, ')', '(', line);
1086 luaK_dischargevars(ls->fs, v);
1087 return;
1088 }
1089 case TK_NAME: {
1090 singlevar(ls, v);
1091 return;
1092 }
1093 default: {
1094 luaX_syntaxerror(ls, "unexpected symbol");
1095 }
1096 }
1097}
1098
1099
1100static void suffixedexp (LexState *ls, expdesc *v) {
1101 /* suffixedexp ->
1102 primaryexp { '.' NAME | '[' exp ']' | ':' NAME funcargs | funcargs } */
1103 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1104 int line = ls->linenumber;
1105 primaryexp(ls, v);
1106 for (;;) {
1107 switch (ls->t.token) {
1108 case '.': { /* fieldsel */
1109 fieldsel(ls, v);
1110 break;
1111 }
1112 case '[': { /* '[' exp ']' */
1113 expdesc key;
1114 luaK_exp2anyregup(fs, v);
1115 yindex(ls, &key);
1116 luaK_indexed(fs, v, &key);
1117 break;
1118 }
1119 case ':': { /* ':' NAME funcargs */
1120 expdesc key;
1121 luaX_next(ls);
1122 codename(ls, &key);
1123 luaK_self(fs, v, &key);
1124 funcargs(ls, v, line);
1125 break;
1126 }
1127 case '(': case TK_STRING: case '{': { /* funcargs */
1128 luaK_exp2nextreg(fs, v);
1129 funcargs(ls, v, line);
1130 break;
1131 }
1132 default: return;
1133 }
1134 }
1135}
1136
1137
1138static void simpleexp (LexState *ls, expdesc *v) {
1139 /* simpleexp -> FLT | INT | STRING | NIL | TRUE | FALSE | ... |
1140 constructor | FUNCTION body | suffixedexp */
1141 switch (ls->t.token) {
1142 case TK_FLT: {
1143 init_exp(v, VKFLT, 0);
1144 v->u.nval = ls->t.seminfo.r;
1145 break;
1146 }
1147 case TK_INT: {
1148 init_exp(v, VKINT, 0);
1149 v->u.ival = ls->t.seminfo.i;
1150 break;
1151 }
1152 case TK_STRING: {
1153 codestring(v, ls->t.seminfo.ts);
1154 break;
1155 }
1156 case TK_NIL: {
1157 init_exp(v, VNIL, 0);
1158 break;
1159 }
1160 case TK_TRUE: {
1161 init_exp(v, VTRUE, 0);
1162 break;
1163 }
1164 case TK_FALSE: {
1165 init_exp(v, VFALSE, 0);
1166 break;
1167 }
1168 case TK_DOTS: { /* vararg */
1169 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1170 check_condition(ls, fs->f->is_vararg,
1171 "cannot use '...' outside a vararg function");
1172 init_exp(v, VVARARG, luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_VARARG, 0, 0, 1));
1173 break;
1174 }
1175 case '{': { /* constructor */
1176 constructor(ls, v);
1177 return;
1178 }
1179 case TK_FUNCTION: {
1180 luaX_next(ls);
1181 body(ls, v, 0, ls->linenumber);
1182 return;
1183 }
1184 default: {
1185 suffixedexp(ls, v);
1186 return;
1187 }
1188 }
1189 luaX_next(ls);
1190}

1193static UnOpr getunopr (int op) {
1194 switch (op) {
1195 case TK_NOT: return OPR_NOT;
1196 case '-': return OPR_MINUS;
1197 case '~': return OPR_BNOT;
1198 case '#': return OPR_LEN;
1199 default: return OPR_NOUNOPR;
1200 }
1201}
1202
1203
1204static BinOpr getbinopr (int op) {
1205 switch (op) {
1206 case '+': return OPR_ADD;
1207 case '-': return OPR_SUB;
1208 case '*': return OPR_MUL;
1209 case '%': return OPR_MOD;
1210 case '^': return OPR_POW;
1211 case '/': return OPR_DIV;
1212 case TK_IDIV: return OPR_IDIV;
1213 case '&': return OPR_BAND;
1214 case '|': return OPR_BOR;
1215 case '~': return OPR_BXOR;
1216 case TK_SHL: return OPR_SHL;
1217 case TK_SHR: return OPR_SHR;
1218 case TK_CONCAT: return OPR_CONCAT;
1219 case TK_NE: return OPR_NE;
1220 case TK_EQ: return OPR_EQ;
1221 case '<': return OPR_LT;
1222 case TK_LE: return OPR_LE;
1223 case '>': return OPR_GT;
1224 case TK_GE: return OPR_GE;
1225 case TK_AND: return OPR_AND;
1226 case TK_OR: return OPR_OR;
1227 default: return OPR_NOBINOPR;
1228 }
1229}
1230
1231
1232/*
1233** Priority table for binary operators.
1234*/
1235static const struct {
1236 lu_byte left; /* left priority for each binary operator */
1237 lu_byte right; /* right priority */
1238} priority[] = { /* ORDER OPR */
1239 {10, 10}, {10, 10}, /* '+' '-' */
1240 {11, 11}, {11, 11}, /* '*' '%' */
1241 {14, 13}, /* '^' (right associative) */
1242 {11, 11}, {11, 11}, /* '/' '//' */
1243 {6, 6}, {4, 4}, {5, 5}, /* '&' '|' '~' */
1244 {7, 7}, {7, 7}, /* '<<' '>>' */
1245 {9, 8}, /* '..' (right associative) */
1246 {3, 3}, {3, 3}, {3, 3}, /* ==, <, <= */
1247 {3, 3}, {3, 3}, {3, 3}, /* ~=, >, >= */
1248 {2, 2}, {1, 1} /* and, or */
1249};
1250
1251#define UNARY_PRIORITY 12 /* priority for unary operators */
1252
1253
1254/*
1255** subexpr -> (simpleexp | unop subexpr) { binop subexpr }
1256** where 'binop' is any binary operator with a priority higher than 'limit'
1257*/
1258static BinOpr subexpr (LexState *ls, expdesc *v, int limit) {
1259 BinOpr op;
1260 UnOpr uop;
1261 enterlevel(ls);
1262 uop = getunopr(ls->t.token);
1263 if (uop != OPR_NOUNOPR) { /* prefix (unary) operator? */
1264 int line = ls->linenumber;
1265 luaX_next(ls); /* skip operator */
1266 subexpr(ls, v, UNARY_PRIORITY);
1267 luaK_prefix(ls->fs, uop, v, line);
1268 }
1269 else simpleexp(ls, v);
1270 /* expand while operators have priorities higher than 'limit' */
1271 op = getbinopr(ls->t.token);
1272 while (op != OPR_NOBINOPR && priority[op].left > limit) {
1273 expdesc v2;
1274 BinOpr nextop;
1275 int line = ls->linenumber;
1276 luaX_next(ls); /* skip operator */
1277 luaK_infix(ls->fs, op, v);
1278 /* read sub-expression with higher priority */
1279 nextop = subexpr(ls, &v2, priority[op].right);
1280 luaK_posfix(ls->fs, op, v, &v2, line);
1281 op = nextop;
1282 }
1283 leavelevel(ls);
1284 return op; /* return first untreated operator */
1285}
1286
1287
1288static void expr (LexState *ls, expdesc *v) {
1289 subexpr(ls, v, 0);
1290}

1313/*
1314** structure to chain all variables in the left-hand side of an
1315** assignment
1316*/
1317struct LHS_assign {
1318 struct LHS_assign *prev;
1319 expdesc v; /* variable (global, local, upvalue, or indexed) */
1320};
1321
1322
1323/*
1324** check whether, in an assignment to an upvalue/local variable, the
1325** upvalue/local variable is begin used in a previous assignment to a
1326** table. If so, save original upvalue/local value in a safe place and
1327** use this safe copy in the previous assignment.
1328*/
1329static void check_conflict (LexState *ls, struct LHS_assign *lh, expdesc *v) {
1330 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1331 int extra = fs->freereg; /* eventual position to save local variable */
1332 int conflict = 0;
1333 for (; lh; lh = lh->prev) { /* check all previous assignments */
1334 if (vkisindexed(lh->v.k)) { /* assignment to table field? */
1335 if (lh->v.k == VINDEXUP) { /* is table an upvalue? */
1336 if (v->k == VUPVAL && lh->v.u.ind.t == v->u.info) {
1337 conflict = 1; /* table is the upvalue being assigned now */
1338 lh->v.k = VINDEXSTR;
1339 lh->v.u.ind.t = extra; /* assignment will use safe copy */
1340 }
1341 }
1342 else { /* table is a register */
1343 if (v->k == VLOCAL && lh->v.u.ind.t == v->u.var.ridx) {
1344 conflict = 1; /* table is the local being assigned now */
1345 lh->v.u.ind.t = extra; /* assignment will use safe copy */
1346 }
1347 /* is index the local being assigned? */
1348 if (lh->v.k == VINDEXED && v->k == VLOCAL &&
1349 lh->v.u.ind.idx == v->u.var.ridx) {
1350 conflict = 1;
1351 lh->v.u.ind.idx = extra; /* previous assignment will use safe copy */
1352 }
1353 }
1354 }
1355 }
1356 if (conflict) {
1357 /* copy upvalue/local value to a temporary (in position 'extra') */
1358 if (v->k == VLOCAL)
1359 luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_MOVE, extra, v->u.var.ridx, 0);
1360 else
1361 luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_GETUPVAL, extra, v->u.info, 0);
1362 luaK_reserveregs(fs, 1);
1363 }
1364}
1365
1366/*
1367** Parse and compile a multiple assignment. The first "variable"
1368** (a 'suffixedexp') was already read by the caller.
1369**
1370** assignment -> suffixedexp restassign
1371** restassign -> ',' suffixedexp restassign | '=' explist
1372*/
1373static void restassign (LexState *ls, struct LHS_assign *lh, int nvars) {
1374 expdesc e;
1375 check_condition(ls, vkisvar(lh->v.k), "syntax error");
1376 check_readonly(ls, &lh->v);
1377 if (testnext(ls, ',')) { /* restassign -> ',' suffixedexp restassign */
1378 struct LHS_assign nv;
1379 nv.prev = lh;
1380 suffixedexp(ls, &nv.v);
1381 if (!vkisindexed(nv.v.k))
1382 check_conflict(ls, lh, &nv.v);
1383 enterlevel(ls); /* control recursion depth */
1384 restassign(ls, &nv, nvars+1);
1385 leavelevel(ls);
1386 }
1387 else { /* restassign -> '=' explist */
1388 int nexps;
1389 checknext(ls, '=');
1390 nexps = explist(ls, &e);
1391 if (nexps != nvars)
1392 adjust_assign(ls, nvars, nexps, &e);
1393 else {
1394 luaK_setoneret(ls->fs, &e); /* close last expression */
1395 luaK_storevar(ls->fs, &lh->v, &e);
1396 return; /* avoid default */
1397 }
1398 }
1399 init_exp(&e, VNONRELOC, ls->fs->freereg-1); /* default assignment */
1400 luaK_storevar(ls->fs, &lh->v, &e);
1401}
1402
1403
1404static int cond (LexState *ls) {
1405 /* cond -> exp */
1406 expdesc v;
1407 expr(ls, &v); /* read condition */
1408 if (v.k == VNIL) v.k = VFALSE; /* 'falses' are all equal here */
1409 luaK_goiftrue(ls->fs, &v);
1410 return v.f;
1411}

1413
1414static void gotostat (LexState *ls) {
1415 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1416 int line = ls->linenumber;
1417 TString *name = str_checkname(ls); /* label's name */
1418 Labeldesc *lb = findlabel(ls, name);
1419 if (lb == NULL) /* no label? */
1420 /* forward jump; will be resolved when the label is declared */
1421 newgotoentry(ls, name, line, luaK_jump(fs));
1422 else { /* found a label */
1423 /* backward jump; will be resolved here */
1424 int lblevel = reglevel(fs, lb->nactvar); /* label level */
1425 if (luaY_nvarstack(fs) > lblevel) /* leaving the scope of a variable? */
1426 luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_CLOSE, lblevel, 0, 0);
1427 /* create jump and link it to the label */
1428 luaK_patchlist(fs, luaK_jump(fs), lb->pc);
1429 }
1430}

1433/*
1434** Break statement. Semantically equivalent to "goto break".
1435*/
1436static void breakstat (LexState *ls) {
1437 int line = ls->linenumber;
1438 luaX_next(ls); /* skip break */
1439 newgotoentry(ls, luaS_newliteral(ls->L, "break"), line, luaK_jump(ls->fs));
1440}

1443/*
1444** Check whether there is already a label with the given 'name'.
1445*/
1446static void checkrepeated (LexState *ls, TString *name) {
1447 Labeldesc *lb = findlabel(ls, name);
1448 if (l_unlikely(lb != NULL)) { /* already defined? */
1449 const char *msg = "label '%s' already defined on line %d";
1450 msg = luaO_pushfstring(ls->L, msg, getstr(name), lb->line);
1451 luaK_semerror(ls, msg); /* error */
1452 }
1453}

1455
1456static void labelstat (LexState *ls, TString *name, int line) {
1457 /* label -> '::' NAME '::' */
1458 checknext(ls, TK_DBCOLON); /* skip double colon */
1459 while (ls->t.token == ';' || ls->t.token == TK_DBCOLON)
1460 statement(ls); /* skip other no-op statements */
1461 checkrepeated(ls, name); /* check for repeated labels */
1462 createlabel(ls, name, line, block_follow(ls, 0));
1463}

1465
1466static void whilestat (LexState *ls, int line) {
1467 /* whilestat -> WHILE cond DO block END */
1468 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1469 int whileinit;
1470 int condexit;
1471 BlockCnt bl;
1472 luaX_next(ls); /* skip WHILE */
1473 whileinit = luaK_getlabel(fs);
1474 condexit = cond(ls);
1475 enterblock(fs, &bl, 1);
1476 checknext(ls, TK_DO);
1477 block(ls);
1478 luaK_jumpto(fs, whileinit);
1479 check_match(ls, TK_END, TK_WHILE, line);
1480 leaveblock(fs);
1481 luaK_patchtohere(fs, condexit); /* false conditions finish the loop */
1482}
1483
1484
1485static void repeatstat (LexState *ls, int line) {
1486 /* repeatstat -> REPEAT block UNTIL cond */
1487 int condexit;
1488 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1489 int repeat_init = luaK_getlabel(fs);
1490 BlockCnt bl1, bl2;
1491 enterblock(fs, &bl1, 1); /* loop block */
1492 enterblock(fs, &bl2, 0); /* scope block */
1493 luaX_next(ls); /* skip REPEAT */
1494 statlist(ls);
1495 check_match(ls, TK_UNTIL, TK_REPEAT, line);
1496 condexit = cond(ls); /* read condition (inside scope block) */
1497 leaveblock(fs); /* finish scope */
1498 if (bl2.upval) { /* upvalues? */
1499 int exit = luaK_jump(fs); /* normal exit must jump over fix */
1500 luaK_patchtohere(fs, condexit); /* repetition must close upvalues */
1501 luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_CLOSE, reglevel(fs, bl2.nactvar), 0, 0);
1502 condexit = luaK_jump(fs); /* repeat after closing upvalues */
1503 luaK_patchtohere(fs, exit); /* normal exit comes to here */
1504 }
1505 luaK_patchlist(fs, condexit, repeat_init); /* close the loop */
1506 leaveblock(fs); /* finish loop */
1507}

1510/*
1511** Read an expression and generate code to put its results in next
1512** stack slot.
1513**
1514*/
1515static void exp1 (LexState *ls) {
1516 expdesc e;
1517 expr(ls, &e);
1518 luaK_exp2nextreg(ls->fs, &e);
1519 lua_assert(e.k == VNONRELOC);
1520}

1523/*
1524** Fix for instruction at position 'pc' to jump to 'dest'.
1525** (Jump addresses are relative in Lua). 'back' true means
1526** a back jump.
1527*/
1528static void fixforjump (FuncState *fs, int pc, int dest, int back) {
1529 Instruction *jmp = &fs->f->code[pc];
1530 int offset = dest - (pc + 1);
1531 if (back)
1532 offset = -offset;
1533 if (l_unlikely(offset > MAXARG_Bx))
1534 luaX_syntaxerror(fs->ls, "control structure too long");
1535 SETARG_Bx(*jmp, offset);
1536}

1538
1539/*
1540** Generate code for a 'for' loop.
1541*/
1542static void forbody (LexState *ls, int base, int line, int nvars, int isgen) {
1543 /* forbody -> DO block */
1544 static const OpCode forprep[2] = {OP_FORPREP, OP_TFORPREP};
1545 static const OpCode forloop[2] = {OP_FORLOOP, OP_TFORLOOP};
1546 BlockCnt bl;
1547 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1548 int prep, endfor;
1549 checknext(ls, TK_DO);
1550 prep = luaK_codeABx(fs, forprep[isgen], base, 0);
1551 enterblock(fs, &bl, 0); /* scope for declared variables */
1552 adjustlocalvars(ls, nvars);
1553 luaK_reserveregs(fs, nvars);
1554 block(ls);
1555 leaveblock(fs); /* end of scope for declared variables */
1556 fixforjump(fs, prep, luaK_getlabel(fs), 0);
1557 if (isgen) { /* generic for? */
1558 luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_TFORCALL, base, 0, nvars);
1559 luaK_fixline(fs, line);
1560 }
1561 endfor = luaK_codeABx(fs, forloop[isgen], base, 0);
1562 fixforjump(fs, endfor, prep + 1, 1);
1563 luaK_fixline(fs, line);
1564}

1566
1567static void fornum (LexState *ls, TString *varname, int line) {
1568 /* fornum -> NAME = exp,exp[,exp] forbody */
1569 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1570 int base = fs->freereg;
1571 new_localvarliteral(ls, "(for state)");
1572 new_localvarliteral(ls, "(for state)");
1573 new_localvarliteral(ls, "(for state)");
1574 new_localvar(ls, varname);
1575 checknext(ls, '=');
1576 exp1(ls); /* initial value */
1577 checknext(ls, ',');
1578 exp1(ls); /* limit */
1579 if (testnext(ls, ','))
1580 exp1(ls); /* optional step */
1581 else { /* default step = 1 */
1582 luaK_int(fs, fs->freereg, 1);
1583 luaK_reserveregs(fs, 1);
1584 }
1585 adjustlocalvars(ls, 3); /* control variables */
1586 forbody(ls, base, line, 1, 0);
1587}
1588
1589
1590static void forlist (LexState *ls, TString *indexname) {
1591 /* forlist -> NAME {,NAME} IN explist forbody */
1592 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1593 expdesc e;
1594 int nvars = 5; /* gen, state, control, toclose, 'indexname' */
1595 int line;
1596 int base = fs->freereg;
1597 /* create control variables */
1598 new_localvarliteral(ls, "(for state)");
1599 new_localvarliteral(ls, "(for state)");
1600 new_localvarliteral(ls, "(for state)");
1601 new_localvarliteral(ls, "(for state)");
1602 /* create declared variables */
1603 new_localvar(ls, indexname);
1604 while (testnext(ls, ',')) {
1605 new_localvar(ls, str_checkname(ls));
1606 nvars++;
1607 }
1608 checknext(ls, TK_IN);
1609 line = ls->linenumber;
1610 adjust_assign(ls, 4, explist(ls, &e), &e);
1611 adjustlocalvars(ls, 4); /* control variables */
1612 marktobeclosed(fs); /* last control var. must be closed */
1613 luaK_checkstack(fs, 3); /* extra space to call generator */
1614 forbody(ls, base, line, nvars - 4, 1);
1615}
1616
1617
1618static void forstat (LexState *ls, int line) {
1619 /* forstat -> FOR (fornum | forlist) END */
1620 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1621 TString *varname;
1622 BlockCnt bl;
1623 enterblock(fs, &bl, 1); /* scope for loop and control variables */
1624 luaX_next(ls); /* skip 'for' */
1625 varname = str_checkname(ls); /* first variable name */
1626 switch (ls->t.token) {
1627 case '=': fornum(ls, varname, line); break;
1628 case ',': case TK_IN: forlist(ls, varname); break;
1629 default: luaX_syntaxerror(ls, "'=' or 'in' expected");
1630 }
1631 check_match(ls, TK_END, TK_FOR, line);
1632 leaveblock(fs); /* loop scope ('break' jumps to this point) */
1633}
1634
1635
1636static void test_then_block (LexState *ls, int *escapelist) {
1637 /* test_then_block -> [IF | ELSEIF] cond THEN block */
1638 BlockCnt bl;
1639 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1640 expdesc v;
1641 int jf; /* instruction to skip 'then' code (if condition is false) */
1642 luaX_next(ls); /* skip IF or ELSEIF */
1643 expr(ls, &v); /* read condition */
1644 checknext(ls, TK_THEN);
1645 if (ls->t.token == TK_BREAK) { /* 'if x then break' ? */
1646 int line = ls->linenumber;
1647 luaK_goiffalse(ls->fs, &v); /* will jump if condition is true */
1648 luaX_next(ls); /* skip 'break' */
1649 enterblock(fs, &bl, 0); /* must enter block before 'goto' */
1650 newgotoentry(ls, luaS_newliteral(ls->L, "break"), line, v.t);
1651 while (testnext(ls, ';')) {} /* skip semicolons */
1652 if (block_follow(ls, 0)) { /* jump is the entire block? */
1653 leaveblock(fs);
1654 return; /* and that is it */
1655 }
1656 else /* must skip over 'then' part if condition is false */
1657 jf = luaK_jump(fs);
1658 }
1659 else { /* regular case (not a break) */
1660 luaK_goiftrue(ls->fs, &v); /* skip over block if condition is false */
1661 enterblock(fs, &bl, 0);
1662 jf = v.f;
1663 }
1664 statlist(ls); /* 'then' part */
1665 leaveblock(fs);
1666 if (ls->t.token == TK_ELSE ||
1667 ls->t.token == TK_ELSEIF) /* followed by 'else'/'elseif'? */
1668 luaK_concat(fs, escapelist, luaK_jump(fs)); /* must jump over it */
1669 luaK_patchtohere(fs, jf);
1670}
1671
1672
1673static void ifstat (LexState *ls, int line) {
1674 /* ifstat -> IF cond THEN block {ELSEIF cond THEN block} [ELSE block] END */
1675 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1676 int escapelist = NO_JUMP; /* exit list for finished parts */
1677 test_then_block(ls, &escapelist); /* IF cond THEN block */
1678 while (ls->t.token == TK_ELSEIF)
1679 test_then_block(ls, &escapelist); /* ELSEIF cond THEN block */
1680 if (testnext(ls, TK_ELSE))
1681 block(ls); /* 'else' part */
1682 check_match(ls, TK_END, TK_IF, line);
1683 luaK_patchtohere(fs, escapelist); /* patch escape list to 'if' end */
1684}

1686
1687static void localfunc (LexState *ls) {
1688 expdesc b;
1689 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1690 int fvar = fs->nactvar; /* function's variable index */
1691 new_localvar(ls, str_checkname(ls)); /* new local variable */
1692 adjustlocalvars(ls, 1); /* enter its scope */
1693 body(ls, &b, 0, ls->linenumber); /* function created in next register */
1694 /* debug information will only see the variable after this point! */
1695 localdebuginfo(fs, fvar)->startpc = fs->pc;
1696}

1698
1699static int getlocalattribute (LexState *ls) {
1700 /* ATTRIB -> ['<' Name '>'] */
1701 if (testnext(ls, '<')) {
1702 const char *attr = getstr(str_checkname(ls));
1703 checknext(ls, '>');
1704 if (strcmp(attr, "const") == 0)
1705 return RDKCONST; /* read-only variable */
1706 else if (strcmp(attr, "close") == 0)
1707 return RDKTOCLOSE; /* to-be-closed variable */
1708 else
1709 luaK_semerror(ls,
1710 luaO_pushfstring(ls->L, "unknown attribute '%s'", attr));
1711 }
1712 return VDKREG; /* regular variable */
1713}
1714
1715
1716static void checktoclose (FuncState *fs, int level) {
1717 if (level != -1) { /* is there a to-be-closed variable? */
1718 marktobeclosed(fs);
1719 luaK_codeABC(fs, OP_TBC, reglevel(fs, level), 0, 0);
1720 }
1721}
1722
1723
1724static void localstat (LexState *ls) {
1725 /* stat -> LOCAL NAME ATTRIB { ',' NAME ATTRIB } ['=' explist] */
1726 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1727 int toclose = -1; /* index of to-be-closed variable (if any) */
1728 Vardesc *var; /* last variable */
1729 int vidx, kind; /* index and kind of last variable */
1730 int nvars = 0;
1731 int nexps;
1732 expdesc e;
1733 do {
1734 vidx = new_localvar(ls, str_checkname(ls));
1735 kind = getlocalattribute(ls);
1736 getlocalvardesc(fs, vidx)->vd.kind = kind;
1737 if (kind == RDKTOCLOSE) { /* to-be-closed? */
1738 if (toclose != -1) /* one already present? */
1739 luaK_semerror(ls, "multiple to-be-closed variables in local list");
1740 toclose = fs->nactvar + nvars;
1741 }
1742 nvars++;
1743 } while (testnext(ls, ','));
1744 if (testnext(ls, '='))
1745 nexps = explist(ls, &e);
1746 else {
1747 e.k = VVOID;
1748 nexps = 0;
1749 }
1750 var = getlocalvardesc(fs, vidx); /* get last variable */
1751 if (nvars == nexps && /* no adjustments? */
1752 var->vd.kind == RDKCONST && /* last variable is const? */
1753 luaK_exp2const(fs, &e, &var->k)) { /* compile-time constant? */
1754 var->vd.kind = RDKCTC; /* variable is a compile-time constant */
1755 adjustlocalvars(ls, nvars - 1); /* exclude last variable */
1756 fs->nactvar++; /* but count it */
1757 }
1758 else {
1759 adjust_assign(ls, nvars, nexps, &e);
1760 adjustlocalvars(ls, nvars);
1761 }
1762 checktoclose(fs, toclose);
1763}
1764
1765
1766static int funcname (LexState *ls, expdesc *v) {
1767 /* funcname -> NAME {fieldsel} [':' NAME] */
1768 int ismethod = 0;
1769 singlevar(ls, v);
1770 while (ls->t.token == '.')
1771 fieldsel(ls, v);
1772 if (ls->t.token == ':') {
1773 ismethod = 1;
1774 fieldsel(ls, v);
1775 }
1776 return ismethod;
1777}
1778
1779
1780static void funcstat (LexState *ls, int line) {
1781 /* funcstat -> FUNCTION funcname body */
1782 int ismethod;
1783 expdesc v, b;
1784 luaX_next(ls); /* skip FUNCTION */
1785 ismethod = funcname(ls, &v);
1786 body(ls, &b, ismethod, line);
1787 check_readonly(ls, &v);
1788 luaK_storevar(ls->fs, &v, &b);
1789 luaK_fixline(ls->fs, line); /* definition "happens" in the first line */
1790}
1791
1792
1793static void exprstat (LexState *ls) {
1794 /* stat -> func | assignment */
1795 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1796 struct LHS_assign v;
1797 suffixedexp(ls, &v.v);
1798 if (ls->t.token == '=' || ls->t.token == ',') { /* stat -> assignment ? */
1799 v.prev = NULL;
1800 restassign(ls, &v, 1);
1801 }
1802 else { /* stat -> func */
1803 Instruction *inst;
1804 check_condition(ls, v.v.k == VCALL, "syntax error");
1805 inst = &getinstruction(fs, &v.v);
1806 SETARG_C(*inst, 1); /* call statement uses no results */
1807 }
1808}
1809
1810
1811static void retstat (LexState *ls) {
1812 /* stat -> RETURN [explist] [';'] */
1813 FuncState *fs = ls->fs;
1814 expdesc e;
1815 int nret; /* number of values being returned */
1816 int first = luaY_nvarstack(fs); /* first slot to be returned */
1817 if (block_follow(ls, 1) || ls->t.token == ';')
1818 nret = 0; /* return no values */
1819 else {
1820 nret = explist(ls, &e); /* optional return values */
1821 if (hasmultret(e.k)) {
1822 luaK_setmultret(fs, &e);
1823 if (e.k == VCALL && nret == 1 && !fs->bl->insidetbc) { /* tail call? */
1824 SET_OPCODE(getinstruction(fs,&e), OP_TAILCALL);
1825 lua_assert(GETARG_A(getinstruction(fs,&e)) == luaY_nvarstack(fs));
1826 }
1827 nret = LUA_MULTRET; /* return all values */
1828 }
1829 else {
1830 if (nret == 1) /* only one single value? */
1831 first = luaK_exp2anyreg(fs, &e); /* can use original slot */
1832 else { /* values must go to the top of the stack */
1833 luaK_exp2nextreg(fs, &e);
1834 lua_assert(nret == fs->freereg - first);
1835 }
1836 }
1837 }
1838 luaK_ret(fs, first, nret);
1839 testnext(ls, ';'); /* skip optional semicolon */
1840}
1841
1842
1843static void statement (LexState *ls) {
1844 int line = ls->linenumber; /* may be needed for error messages */
1845 enterlevel(ls);
1846 switch (ls->t.token) {
1847 case ';': { /* stat -> ';' (empty statement) */
1848 luaX_next(ls); /* skip ';' */
1849 break;
1850 }
1851 case TK_IF: { /* stat -> ifstat */
1852 ifstat(ls, line);
1853 break;
1854 }
1855 case TK_WHILE: { /* stat -> whilestat */
1856 whilestat(ls, line);
1857 break;
1858 }
1859 case TK_DO: { /* stat -> DO block END */
1860 luaX_next(ls); /* skip DO */
1861 block(ls);
1862 check_match(ls, TK_END, TK_DO, line);
1863 break;
1864 }
1865 case TK_FOR: { /* stat -> forstat */
1866 forstat(ls, line);
1867 break;
1868 }
1869 case TK_REPEAT: { /* stat -> repeatstat */
1870 repeatstat(ls, line);
1871 break;
1872 }
1873 case TK_FUNCTION: { /* stat -> funcstat */
1874 funcstat(ls, line);
1875 break;
1876 }
1877 case TK_LOCAL: { /* stat -> localstat */
1878 luaX_next(ls); /* skip LOCAL */
1879 if (testnext(ls, TK_FUNCTION)) /* local function? */
1880 localfunc(ls);
1881 else
1882 localstat(ls);
1883 break;
1884 }
1885 case TK_DBCOLON: { /* stat -> label */
1886 luaX_next(ls); /* skip double colon */
1887 labelstat(ls, str_checkname(ls), line);
1888 break;
1889 }
1890 case TK_RETURN: { /* stat -> retstat */
1891 luaX_next(ls); /* skip RETURN */
1892 retstat(ls);
1893 break;
1894 }
1895 case TK_BREAK: { /* stat -> breakstat */
1896 breakstat(ls);
1897 break;
1898 }
1899 case TK_GOTO: { /* stat -> 'goto' NAME */
1900 luaX_next(ls); /* skip 'goto' */
1901 gotostat(ls);
1902 break;
1903 }
1904 default: { /* stat -> func | assignment */
1905 exprstat(ls);
1906 break;
1907 }
1908 }
1909 lua_assert(ls->fs->f->maxstacksize >= ls->fs->freereg &&
1910 ls->fs->freereg >= luaY_nvarstack(ls->fs));
1911 ls->fs->freereg = luaY_nvarstack(ls->fs); /* free registers */
1912 leavelevel(ls);
1913}

1915/* }====================================================================== */

1917
1918/*
1919** compiles the main function, which is a regular vararg function with an
1920** upvalue named LUA_ENV
1921*/
1922static void mainfunc (LexState *ls, FuncState *fs) {
1923 BlockCnt bl;
1924 Upvaldesc *env;
1925 open_func(ls, fs, &bl);
1926 setvararg(fs, 0); /* main function is always declared vararg */
1927 env = allocupvalue(fs); /* ...set environment upvalue */
1928 env->instack = 1;
1929 env->idx = 0;
1930 env->kind = VDKREG;
1931 env->name = ls->envn;
1932 luaC_objbarrier(ls->L, fs->f, env->name);
1933 luaX_next(ls); /* read first token */
1934 statlist(ls); /* parse main body */
1935 check(ls, TK_EOS);
1936 close_func(ls);
1937}

1939
1940LClosure *luaY_parser (lua_State *L, ZIO *z, Mbuffer *buff,
1941 Dyndata *dyd, const char *name, int firstchar) {
1942 LexState lexstate;
1943 FuncState funcstate;
1944 LClosure *cl = luaF_newLclosure(L, 1); /* create main closure */
